The paper focuses on the estimation of low-complexity signals observed through quantized compressive measurements, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields. The use of quantization suggests that the paper may belong to cs.IT (Information Theory), while the focus on signal and matrix estimation suggests cs.SP (Signal Processing). The use of low-rank matrices and compressible signals suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the use of Basis Pursuit Denoise and proximal algorithms suggests cs.MM (Mathematical Methods). Finally, the use of numerical simulations suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.SP, followed by cs.LG, cs.MM, and cs.NA.
